rch too early;• and more.Written by experts in the field of early child development, care, and education, the book is essential reading for parents and policymakers alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBrainxResearchxSocial aspects. 0aCerveauxRecherchexAspect social. 0aChild development. 0aChild welfarexUnited States. 0aChild welfarezUnited States. 0aEnfantsxDéveloppement. 0aEnfantsxProtection, assistance, etcxÉtats-Unis. 0aFamily policyxUnited States. 0aFamily policyzUnited States. 0aInfantsxDevelopment. 0aNourrissonsxDéveloppement. 0aPolitique familialexÉtats-Unis. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Developmental / Child.2bisacsh1 aFinn-Stevenson, Matia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHall, Nancy W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012739340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127393423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300127393/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles